result.name: Chung Shing Thai Restaurant

reviews.text: One of the best Thai restaurants in the new territories. Family run and food has been consistent. Been going to this place for decades.

I first visited this place when it was just a local convenient store back in the 1980s (yes I’m old). And it serves no more than take-away lunch boxes. Now they serve good Thai food in a semi-outdoor alfresco atmosphere. I would not say food here are top notch, but they’re quite good. Staff are friendly too. There’s usually a line, so be patient please. You can phone in and book a table too.
Food ingredients are market fresh. Kitchen employees are mostly Thai which is an important element to produce the right native tastes for their wide menu.
Do you want to have good food for a good price? Then this is the place to be! Satay was for me the best dish, however, the rest wasn't bad at all!
Very popular Thai restaurant. Food not the most authentic, tastes delicious nonetheless. Expect a queue during peak dining hours.

result.name: 忠誠茶座

reviews.text: One of the best Thai restaurants in the new territories. Family run and food has been consistent. Been going to this place for decades.
食物味道，質素唔錯，多選擇，步行3~5分鐘有停車場，附近有單車可租，適合一家大小，朋友聚會，不過，自己揸車比較方便。
食物仍然美味但份量少了很多,不是假日的中午有很多吉枱,因附近開了些不同種類的食肆
這個茶座環境很好附近又有停車埸交通都算方便食品都0K價錢大眾化附近又有單租玩又有小艇出租一家老少到此遊玩都可以。
環境舒服~有冷氣！ 是日假日午飯時段 不用等位
